%section.tbs-section
  %h1.page-header#header Header
  %p.lead
    The
    %code tb_header
    helper is provided to create
    uniform application headers.

  %h3#header-example Basic Example

  .tbs-example
    = tb_header app_name: 'My App'
  .highlight
    :markdown
          = tb_header app_name: 'My App'

  %h3#header-options All Options
  %p
    The following options can be used with the helper:

  %dl.dl-horizontal
    %dt app_name
    %dd
      The name of your application; defaults to the Rails app name.

    %dt app_root
    %dd
      The root URL for your application, defaults to /

    %dt hamburger
    %dd
      Boolean; does not render the internal apps hamburger menu if
      %code false

    %dt logo_side
    %dd
      %code :left
      or
      %code :right
      &mdash;
      determines which side of the application
      name the logo sits on.
      Defaults left, but sometimes
      (as in "Inside TED")
      the application name should come first.
